title: For Sale:  Ruger Gunsite Scout, Stainless
postcontent: I have for sale a nearly new Ruger Gunsite Scout. It's the 18" Stainless Steel variant, it comes with a Burris 2-7 long eye relief scout scope, a sling, a soft-case and 3 magazines. The 18" barrel length is superior to the 16" option because there is a significant increase in muzzle blast and reduction in velocity when losing those two inches. Stainless steel and a laminate stock also means that this is a truly rugged rifle. No need to worry about rust or warping the stock. The scout scope is attached using quick detach scope mounts, so if you're ever in a situation where the scope is damaged, but you still need to take a shot, you can remove the scope and use the fantastic ghost ring iron sights. Ruger designed the GSR to be adjustable to nearly any body type; this means that the rifle comes with spacers that can either increase, or decrease the length of pull (length from butt-pad to trigger). I am not interested in a trade. And all purchases will obviously be done through a licensed FFL, purchaser to pay the transfer fees.
